                    <!--Carcasa-->
                <h3>Choosing the case and cooling system</h3>
                <p>It may not look like it, but the case is an important factor in building a personal computer.</p>
                <p>Major manufacturers of enclosures and cooling systems on the market include: Cooler Master, NZXT, Aqirys, Corsair, Lian Li, Be Quiet!, Thermaltake.</p>
                <p>Whether you intend to assemble a computer for gaming or office, the case has the same roles of protecting the rest of the components from dust and other external factors and maintaining the coolest temperature.</p>
                <p>Case enclosures have come to be fitted with a variety of cooling systems, from MOLEX or 4-pin plug fans to complex liquid-cooled systems (AIO, used especially in computers with high-performance components).</p>
                <p>They are also equipped with special slots for: power supply (can be positioned up/down), motherboard, video card outputs, HDD, SSD, additional fans, DVD-ROM</p>
